SIMPLE: prevaricator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prevaricator
<hw>Pre*var"i*ca`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praevaricator</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧varicateur</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who prevaricates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Roman Law)</fld> <def>A sham dealer; one who
colludes with a defendant in a sham prosecution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who betrays or abuses a trust.</def>
<rj><au>Prynne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preve</ent>⟦br⟧
